<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you realize you&#8217;ve lost an item or a document, the first thing to do is stay calm. You can manage the situation better by following the steps below:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Assess the Situation</strong>: Think about when and where you might have lost your item or document. Remembering where you last saw it can increase your chances of finding it.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Notify Local Authorities</strong>: If the lost item or document is important, contact the nearest local authorities or the police. There are police stations in every city in Turkey.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Contact Relevant Institutions</strong>: Especially for lost documents, it&#8217;s necessary to contact the relevant institution (e.g., your university, consulate).</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also find our article on <a title="Night Travel and Safety Precautions in Turkey" href="https://https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-gece-seyahati-guvenlik-onlemleri/">Night Travel and Safety Precautions in Turkey</a> helpful.</p>
<h2 id="kaybolan-esyalar-icin-yerel-iletisim-noktalari" class="wp-block-heading">Local Contact Points for Lost Items</h2>
<p data-start="316" data-end="766">When you lose an item in Turkey, it&#8217;s important to act systematically instead of panicking. In every city, municipalities, public transport authorities, and police departments officially handle lost item reports.<br data-start="522" data-end="525" />As a first step, try to remember where you lost the item. If you lost it on public transport like a bus, metro, or metrobus, you can fill out an online form on the relevant authority&#8217;s <strong data-start="686" data-end="712">“<a href="https://www.turkiye.gov.tr/iett-kayip-esya-bildirimi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lost Item Report</a>”</strong> page.</p>
<h3 data-start="768" data-end="992">Reporting a Lost Item via e-Devlet</h3>
<p data-start="768" data-end="992">To officially report your lost items, you can use the <a class="decorated-link cursor-pointer" target="_new" rel="noopener" data-start="857" data-end="942">e-Devlet Lost Item Report</a> service. Through this system, you can:</p>
<ul data-start="993" data-end="1165">
<li data-start="993" data-end="1047">
<p data-start="995" data-end="1047">Report the items you have lost,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1048" data-end="1098">
<p data-start="1050" data-end="1098">View your previous reports,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1099" data-end="1165">
<p data-start="1101" data-end="1165">Get information about the retrieval process if your item has been found.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1167" data-end="1637">IETT Found Item Procedure</h3>
<p data-start="1167" data-end="1637">In Istanbul, items lost on public transport are collected and stored for a certain period according to the <a class="decorated-link cursor-pointer" target="_new" rel="noopener" data-start="1250" data-end="1334">IETT Found Item Directive</a>.<br data-start="1382" data-end="1385" />If you lost an item on an IETT vehicle, you can contact the nearest <strong>Regional Office</strong> or the <strong>Central Found Items Office</strong>.<br data-start="1519" data-end="1522" />Items with special or legal value, such as weapons, IDs, or bank cards, are handed over <strong>directly to the police departments</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-start="1639" data-end="2071">For Documents Lost in Healthcare Institutions</h3>
<p data-start="1639" data-end="2071">If you are a healthcare worker or institutional staff and a device, paper, or document is lost, the procedure is carried out according to the <a class="decorated-link cursor-pointer" target="_new" rel="noopener" data-start="1779" data-end="1876">Ministry of Health&#8217;s relevant circular</a>.<br data-start="1896" data-end="1899" />According to this, an incident report must be prepared, local law enforcement (police or gendarmerie) must be contacted, and the Public Prosecutor&#8217;s Office must be informed if necessary.</p>
<h3 data-start="1670" data-end="1718">Lost Item Procedures at Airports</h3>
<p data-start="1719" data-end="1913">Items lost at airports are usually collected by “<strong>Lost and Found</strong>” offices and stored for a limited time.<br data-start="1863" data-end="1866" />The process varies slightly at each airport:</p>
<ul data-start="1915" data-end="2595">
<li data-start="1915" data-end="2202">
<p data-start="1917" data-end="2202"><strong data-start="1917" data-end="1947">Istanbul Airport (İGA):</strong><br data-start="1947" data-end="1950" />You can fill out an online form on the <a class="decorated-link cursor-pointer" href="https://www.istairport.com/en/services/discover/lost-and-found-inquiry-form/?locale=en" target="_new" rel="noopener" data-start="1952" data-end="2037">İGA Lost &#038; Found</a> page or visit the “Lost and Found Office” inside the terminal.<br data-start="2148" data-end="2151" />Items are generally stored for <strong data-start="2172" data-end="2182">30 days</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2203" data-end="2384">
<p data-start="2205" data-end="2384"><strong data-start="2205" data-end="2234">Sabiha Gökçen Airport:</strong><br data-start="2234" data-end="2237" />Reports can be made via email or phone through the Sabiha Gökçen Lost and Found Service.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2385" data-end="2595">
<p data-start="2387" data-end="2595"><strong data-start="2387" data-end="2423">Airports in other cities</strong> (such as Ankara Esenboğa, İzmir Adnan Menderes, Antalya Airport, etc.), you should visit the “Lost &#038; Found” section on the respective airport&#8217;s official website.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-vize-belgelerinizi-kaybettiyseniz-ne-yapmalisiniz" class="wp-block-heading">What to Do If You Lose Your Visa Documents in Turkey?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Losing your visa documents can be a serious problem for international students and visitors. You can resolve the situation by following these steps:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Contact Your Consulate</strong>: If you&#8217;ve lost your visa documents, contact your nearest consulate or embassy. They will assist you in reissuing the lost documents.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Prepare the Necessary Documents</strong>: The following documents are generally required to obtain a new visa:</li>
<li>Passport</li>
<li>A photocopy of the lost visa document (if available)</li>
<li>New visa application form</li>
<li>Financial documents</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Follow Up on the Application Process</strong>: After reviewing your documents, the consulate will issue <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/vize-ikamet-izni-surecleri/">your new visa document</a>. This process can typically take a few weeks.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-kaybolan-esyalar-icin-sigorta-surecleri" class="wp-block-heading">Insurance Processes for Lost Items in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your lost item is insured, you can follow these steps to start the insurance process:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Check Your Insurance Policy</strong>: Check whether your lost item is <a href="_wp_link_placeholder" data-wplink-edit="true">covered by your policy</a>.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Contact Your Insurance Company</strong>: Get in touch with your insurance company to report the situation. Prepare the necessary documents (e.g., loss report, receipts).</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Complete the Claim Process</strong>: The insurance company will review your claim for the lost item and, if approved, will pay out the compensation.</p>
<h2 id="kaybolan-esyalar-ve-belgeler-icin-online-basvuru-surecleri" class="wp-block-heading">Online Application Processes for Lost Items and Documents</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Today, many procedures can be completed online. The online application processes for lost items and documents in Turkey are as follows:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Police Website</strong>: You can file an online report for lost items on the official website of the Turkish National Police. This can be useful for keeping a record of your lost items.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Insurance Company Online Services</strong>: If your lost item is insured, you can file a claim on your insurance company&#8217;s website.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Consulate or Embassy Websites</strong>: In case of lost visa documents, you can apply online through the website of the relevant consulate or embassy.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What documents are required for lost items in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Generally, an identification document and a loss report are required for lost items. For insured items, the insurance policy may also be necessary.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What process should be followed for lost documents?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For lost documents, you need to contact the nearest consulate or the relevant institution, prepare the necessary documents, and submit an application.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the recovery rate for lost items in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The recovery rate for lost items varies depending on where the item was lost and the circumstances. However, the police and relevant institutions generally work to find lost belongings.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long should I wait for a lost item?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The waiting period for a lost item can vary depending on the situation. It&#8217;s important to follow the instructions provided by the office where you filed the report.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long does the reapplication process for lost documents take in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The reapplication process for lost documents can take several weeks, depending on the type of document and the processing time of the relevant institution.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-04-08T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:50:49Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'procedures-for-lost-items-and-documents-in-turkey' );
