guage":"fr-FR","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2/","name":"Comment célèbre-t-on le Nouvel An en Turquie ? - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-06T05:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-06T12:11:38+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor.webp"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"fr-FR"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Comment célèbre-t-on le Nouvel An en Turquie ? - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-06T05:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-06T12:11:38+03:00","articleSection":"Vie étudiante et Voyages","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Vous prévoyez de passer le Nouvel An en Turquie ? Quelle chance ! Le pays regorge d&#039;options aussi diverses qu&#039;amusantes pour célébrer la dernière nuit de l&#039;année. [&hellip;]","name":"Comment célèbre-t-on le Nouvel An en Turquie ? - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor.webp"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p>Vous prévoyez de passer le réveillon du Nouvel An en Turquie ? Vous avez de la chance, car ce pays regorge d&#8217;options diverses et amusantes pour célébrer la dernière nuit de l&#8217;année. Si vous vous demandez « Que faire le soir du Nouvel An ? », cette liste est faite pour vous.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Le dîner traditionnel du Nouvel An : dinde, mezzés et longues files d&#8217;attente</h2>
<p>En Turquie, qui dit Nouvel An dit souvent <strong>dinde rôtie</strong>. Elle est généralement servie avec du pilaf ou du boulgour. Si la fête a lieu à la maison, les invités apportent souvent divers mezzés ou salades. Il est donc tout à fait normal de voir de longues files d&#8217;attente chez les traiteurs et dans les supermarchés le jour du réveillon.</p>
<p>Le dîner se déroule devant les émissions spéciales du Nouvel An à la télévision, suivi de jeux amusants. Le « Tombala », l&#8217;équivalent du bingo, est un classique nostalgique dans de nombreux foyers.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Détails culturels : sous-vêtements rouges, grenades et superstitions</h2>
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="772" src="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kulturel-detaylar-kirmizi-ic-camasiri-nar-ve-sans-inanclari-1024x772.webp" alt="Détails culturels pour le Nouvel An en Turquie : sous-vêtements rouges et grenades pour porter chance." class="wp-image-10971" srcset="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kulturel-detaylar-kirmizi-ic-camasiri-nar-ve-sans-inanclari-1024x772.webp 1024w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kulturel-detaylar-kirmizi-ic-camasiri-nar-ve-sans-inanclari-300x226.webp 300w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kulturel-detaylar-kirmizi-ic-camasiri-nar-ve-sans-inanclari-768x579.webp 768w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kulturel-detaylar-kirmizi-ic-camasiri-nar-ve-sans-inanclari.webp 1168w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<p>Il existe des croyances intéressantes que les Turcs adoptent pour le Nouvel An. Porter ou offrir des <strong>sous-vêtements rouges</strong> est censé porter chance pour la nouvelle année. Il est très probable que vous voyiez des rayons entiers de lingerie rouge dans les magasins à cette période.</p>
<p>Une autre tradition consiste à <strong>casser une grenade</strong>. On jette une grenade par terre devant sa porte, un geste symbolique censé apporter abondance et prospérité pour la nouvelle année.</p>
<p>Offrir de petits cadeaux à ses proches est également très courant. Ce sont généralement des présents symboliques et chaleureux : un pull, une écharpe chaude ou une tasse sur le thème du Nouvel An.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Célébrations sur les places publiques et dans les hôtels : foule, ferveur et concerts</h2>
<p>Le soir du Nouvel An est très animé dans les grandes villes. Dans des quartiers d&#8217;<strong>Istanbul comme Ortaköy, Taksim et Beşiktaş</strong>, les gens se rassemblent pour admirer les feux d&#8217;artifice. Mais attention : les routes sont extrêmement bondées, il est donc conseillé de partir tôt. Sinon, comme beaucoup, vous risquez de passer le cap de la nouvelle année dans les embouteillages.</p>
<p>Des aménagements spéciaux peuvent être mis en place sur les lignes de métro le soir du réveillon. Vous pouvez consulter les informations à jour sur le site de <a href="https://www.metro.istanbul/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Metro Istanbul</a>.</p>
<p>De nombreux <strong>hôtels de luxe et salles de concert</strong> organisent de grands événements. Par exemple :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Crowne Hotel</strong> : Hülya Avşar sera sur scène</li>
<li><strong>WOW Hotel</strong> : İbrahim Tatlıses et Serdar Ortaç</li>
<li><strong>Grand Tarabya</strong> : Levent Yüksel</li>
<li><strong>Marriott Şişli</strong> : Ajda Pekkan</li>
</ul>
<p>De nombreuses célébrités se produisent également dans des villes comme la Cappadoce et Antalya.</p>
<p>Les hôtels proposent généralement des forfaits incluant un dîner de gala, de la musique live, une nuitée et un brunch le lendemain matin. Les prix varient, mais pensez à réserver à l&#8217;avance.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Escapade dans une station de montagne sous la neige</h2>
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="772" src="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/karlar-altinda-bir-dag-kasabasina-kacamak-yap-1024x772.webp" alt="Un chalet de montagne sous la neige, une destination idéale pour le Nouvel An en Turquie." class="wp-image-10969" srcset="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/karlar-altinda-bir-dag-kasabasina-kacamak-yap-1024x772.webp 1024w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/karlar-altinda-bir-dag-kasabasina-kacamak-yap-300x226.webp 300w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/karlar-altinda-bir-dag-kasabasina-kacamak-yap-768x579.webp 768w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/karlar-altinda-bir-dag-kasabasina-kacamak-yap.webp 1168w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<p>Que diriez-vous de faire coïncider vos vacances d&#8217;hiver avec le Nouvel An pour commencer l&#8217;année face à un paysage montagneux immaculé ? Les stations de ski comme Uludağ (Bursa), Kartalkaya (Bolu) et Erciyes (Kayseri) sont très populaires pour le réveillon. Mais pas besoin d&#8217;être un skieur invétéré. Passer du temps dans un chalet avec cheminée, en admirant la neige tomber, suffit à ressourcer l&#8217;esprit.</p>
<p>Ces destinations sont facilement accessibles en bus. Vous pouvez consulter les trajets à des prix abordables sur <a href="https://www.obilet.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Obilet</a>. Cependant, il est essentiel d&#8217;acheter vos billets à l&#8217;avance, car ils s&#8217;épuisent rapidement pendant la semaine du Nouvel An.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Croisières sur le Bosphore : fête, paysages et feux d&#8217;artifice</h2>
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="772" src="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bogaz-turlari-eglence-manzara-ve-havai-fisek-bir-arada-1024x772.webp" alt="Feux d''artifice du Nouvel An au-dessus du Bosphore à Istanbul." class="wp-image-10967" srcset="https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bogaz-turlari-eglence-manzara-ve-havai-fisek-bir-arada-1024x772.webp 1024w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bogaz-turlari-eglence-manzara-ve-havai-fisek-bir-arada-300x226.webp 300w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bogaz-turlari-eglence-manzara-ve-havai-fisek-bir-arada-768x579.webp 768w, https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bogaz-turlari-eglence-manzara-ve-havai-fisek-bir-arada.webp 1168w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<p>L&#8217;une des manières les plus mémorables de fêter le Nouvel An à Istanbul est une <strong>croisière sur le Bosphore</strong>. Dîner, performance de DJ ou musique live, danse et, à minuit pile, le spectacle des feux d&#8217;artifice au-dessus du Bosphore&#8230; Il existe des options pour tous les budgets et tous les goûts.</p>
<p>Entrer dans la nouvelle année avec une vue sur le palais de Dolmabahçe depuis le Bosphore pourrait bien être l&#8217;un des moments les plus « instagrammables » de votre réveillon en Turquie.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Si vous n&#8217;aimez pas la foule</h2>
<p>Si vous êtes du genre à dire « Je n&#8217;ai pas envie de foule pour ce Nouvel An, je veux juste être tranquille à la maison », alors un plaid, un thé chaud et un marathon de films pourraient être votre programme idéal. Vous trouverez de nombreux films sur le thème des fêtes sur Netflix, MUBI ou BluTV.</p>
<p>Pendant votre film, vous pouvez goûter à des en-cas turcs. Par exemple : leblebi (pois chiches grillés), çekirdek (graines de tournesol), fındık (noisettes) ou le börek, un classique de la cuisine locale. Les supermarchés proposent aussi des coffrets d&#8217;apéritifs spéciaux pour le Nouvel An.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Questions fréquentes</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quand a lieu le jour férié du Nouvel An en Turquie ?</h3>
<p>Comme chaque année, <strong>le 31 décembre (le réveillon) n&#8217;est pas un jour férié officiel</strong>, mais de nombreuses personnes terminent leur journée plus tôt pour commencer les célébrations. En revanche, <strong>le 1er janvier est un jour férié officiel</strong>, et la plupart des entreprises et des écoles sont fermées. Lorsque le Nouvel An tombe près d&#8217;un week-end, cela crée une opportunité de long week-end, ce qui rend les hôtels et les routes particulièrement bondés.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Comment les Turcs fêtent-ils le Nouvel An ?</h3>
<p>Ils l&#8217;accueillent avec des fêtes à la maison, du tombala (bingo), des feux d&#8217;artifice, des concerts et le traditionnel repas du réveillon. Casser une grenade et porter des sous-vêtements rouges font également partie des rituels pour attirer la chance.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Est-ce une bonne idée de passer le réveillon du Nouvel An en Turquie ?</h3>
<p>Oui, c&#8217;est une expérience très amusante et sûre. Entre les célébrations sur les places publiques, les croisières sur le Bosphore, les concerts et les fêtes chaleureuses à la maison, il y en a pour tous les goûts.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Où fêter le Nouvel An en Turquie ?</h3>
<p>Les places publiques d&#8217;Istanbul, Ankara et Izmir sont très populaires. Des célébrations spéciales ont également lieu dans des destinations touristiques comme Uludağ et la Cappadoce.</p></p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-06T02:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-06T09:11:38Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor.webp","alt":"Comment célèbre-t-on le Nouvel An en Turquie ?","title":"turkler-yeni-yili-nasil-kutluyor"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'comment-celebre-t-on-le-nouvel-an-en-turquie-2' );
UPDATE "ec_pages" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","description":"Balıkesir University was established in Balıkesir on July 11, 1992, under Law No. 3837. Its roots trace back to 1910 with the foundation of Karesi Teacher","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Balıkesir University was established in Balıkesir on July 11, 1992, under Law No. 3837. Its roots trace back to 1910 with the foundation of Karesi Teacher","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Balıkesir University was established in Balıkesir on July 11, 1992, under Law No. 3837. Its roots trace back to 1910 with the foundation of Karesi Teacher","canonicalPath":"/en/balikesir-university/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/balikesir-universitesi-tanitim-rehberi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/balikesir-university/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/balikesir-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/balikesir-university/","name":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-12-30T17:48:49+03:00","dateModified":"2025-12-30T17:48:49+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Balıkesir University","datePublished":"2025-12-30T17:48:49+03:00","dateModified":"2025-12-30T17:48:49+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Balıkesir University was established in Balıkesir on July 11, 1992, under Law No. 3837. Its roots trace back to 1910 with the foundation of Karesi Teacher","name":"Balıkesir University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/balikesir-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/balikesir-university/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/balikesir-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.balikesir.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Balıkesir University</a> was established in Balıkesir on July 11, 1992, under Law No. 3837. Its roots trace back to 1910 with the foundation of Karesi Teacher Training School. In 1932, this institution moved into the building of today&#8217;s Necatibey Faculty of Education. In 1982, it became affiliated with Uludağ University under the name Necatibey Faculty of Education. That same year, Balıkesir State Engineering and Architecture Academy and the School of Business and Tourism were also incorporated into Uludağ University. In 1992, Balıkesir University gained independent status as a legal entity. The university began under the leadership of its first rector, Prof. Dr. Ramazan Özkaya, and is currently led by Prof. Dr. Yücel Acer (since 2023). The university follows the vision of being “contemporary in education, science, and art,” with a mission to support regional development. With approximately 35,000 students (YÖK Atlas, 2022–2023), the university is ranked in the 801–1000 band by Times Higher Education 2025.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Balıkesir University offers a broad academic spectrum through 13 faculties: Medicine, Engineering, Science and Literature, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Education, Theology, Fine Arts, Sports Sciences, Health Sciences, Dentistry, Tourism, Architecture, and Veterinary Medicine. In addition, it has 3 graduate institutes (Science, Social Sciences, Health Sciences), 3 schools, and 12 vocational schools. There are over 200 undergraduate and associate programs, and more than 100 graduate programs. Medicine and Engineering stand out with instruction in English. With nearly 1,500 academic staff, the university offers both theoretical and applied education. Over 100 laboratories and 25 research centers support scientific work. For more details, visit the official website of Balıkesir University.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main campus of Balıkesir University is the Çağış Campus, located 17 kilometers from the city center along the Bigadiç road, covering 1,500 acres. Necatibey Faculty of Education is located downtown, and there are additional campuses in districts like Altınoluk and Ayvalık. With 400,000 m² of indoor space, the campuses are equipped with high-speed internet and smart classrooms. The library offers access to 200,000 printed sources and over one million digital publications, and has a seating capacity of 1,500. The Faculty of Medicine is integrated with the Training and Research Hospital. The university&#8217;s Technopark and Design Center strengthen industry collaboration. The campus provides a modern, technology-rich learning environment.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Dormitories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Balıkesir University does not operate its own dormitories on campus but offers accommodation in collaboration with KYK (Credit and Dormitories Institution). The Çağış Campus area has over 7,000 beds available. Rooms accommodate 2–6 students and include a bed, wardrobe, desk, and internet access. Facilities include laundry rooms, kitchens, and study areas. Security is ensured with 24/7 surveillance, and cleaning is done regularly. Applications are made through the KYK system, with priority given to scholarship students. Private dormitories and rental apartments also serve as alternatives.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Balıkesir University offers a dynamic social environment. The green spaces, sports facilities, and modern setting of the Çağış Campus are noteworthy. Sports areas include basketball, volleyball, and football fields, and student teams participate in tournaments. Dining halls offer daily meals, and various cafés are available on campus. With over 50 student clubs (e.g., music, technology), the university organizes festivals and the annual “Spring Festival.” Balıkesir’s location between the Aegean and Marmara seas enriches student life. Cultural events are held for international students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students looking to learn more about university life in Turkey can visit the Road to Study platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Balıkesir University hosts nearly 1,000 international students from over 40 countries. The International Relations Office provides visa support and orientation services. Turkish language courses are offered by TOMER, and most programs are available in English. The university collaborates with over 150 institutions through Erasmus+, Mevlana, and Farabi programs. &#8220;International Day&#8221; events promote cultural exchange. The hospitality of the local community helps international students adapt more easily.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Security</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In partnership with its Training and Research Hospital, Balıkesir University offers healthcare services with a capacity of 500 beds. The on-campus Health Center provides emergency services, supported by 24/7 ambulance availability. The Psychological Counseling Unit offers individual therapy sessions. The campus is monitored 24/7 with security personnel and surveillance systems.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Çağış Campus of Balıkesir University is located 17 kilometers from the city center. Municipal buses, shared taxis (dolmuş), and university shuttle services operate regularly from 07:00 to 23:00. The campus is 180 kilometers from Izmir Adnan Menderes Airport and 10 kilometers from the main bus terminal. Public transport offers student discounts.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Balıkesir University provides internships and career opportunities through its Career Center and organizes “Career Days.” Academic advisors provide ongoing guidance. The Psychological Support Unit offers free therapy services. The Disability Support Unit coordinates accessibility arrangements. The Scholarship Office manages financial aid and scholarship opportunities.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-12-30T14:48:49Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-04T14:49:34Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'balikesir-university';
