niversitesi-tanitim-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/artvin-coruh-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">A Unique Educational Experience in the Black Sea Region</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University is a public institution located in Artvin, a city in Turkey’s Black Sea Region near the Caucasus. Surrounded by natural beauty and offering diverse academic programs and region-specific opportunities, the university provides a distinctive educational experience for prospective students. This text serves as a detailed guide, from the university’s history to campus life.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University was established on May 17, 2007, through Law No. 5662, which amended the Law on the Organization of Higher Education Institutions. Its establishment was made official in the Official Gazette on May 29, 2007 (Issue No. 26536). Formerly a part of Karadeniz Technical University, it became an independent institution and took its name from the famous Çoruh River. The first rector, Prof. Dr. Mehmet Duman, was appointed in 2008. The current rector, as of March 19, 2025, is Prof. Dr. Mustafa Sıtkı Bilgin (please refer to official sources for updates). The university’s vision is to become a nationally and internationally recognized center of science. Its mission is to contribute to regional and national development through knowledge production. It is particularly known for its specialization in the field of “Medicinal and Aromatic Plants.”</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.artvin.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artvin Çoruh University</a> offers a wide range of academic programs. Faculties include Education, Science and Literature, Theology, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Engineering, Forestry, Health Sciences, Art and Design, Sports Sciences, and Tourism. There are also 7 vocational schools and a graduate institute. As of 2025, the university offers more than 50 undergraduate and associate degree programs. Approximately 400 academic staff members support education with facilities such as the Central Research Laboratory. According to YÖK Atlas, over 5,500 students were enrolled during the 2021–2022 academic year; this number may vary annually. Erasmus+ and Farabi programs offer domestic and international opportunities. For more information, refer to the university’s official sources.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main campus of Artvin Çoruh University is the Seyitler Campus, located 3 km from the city center along the Çoruh River. Additional campuses are located in Hopa, Arhavi, and the city center. The Seyitler Campus features modern lecture halls, laboratories, and a library. The Science and Technology Application and Research Center (BİLTEKMER) supports R&amp;D activities. The library houses 43,000 printed resources and provides access to digital databases such as EBSCO. The campus’s technological infrastructure includes smart classrooms and internet access. Eco-friendly practices enhance the sustainability of the campus. Prospective students can enjoy a peaceful educational environment surrounded by Artvin’s unique natural landscape.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Accommodation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University offers a variety of accommodation options. KYK (Credit and Dormitories Institution) dormitories near the campus provide affordable and safe housing. These dorms include dining halls, internet access, and study areas. The university also offers guidance to help students adapt to city life. While private dorms are limited in Artvin, rental apartments serve as alternatives. After being admitted, students can apply for KYK dormitories. The campus location makes accommodation options easily accessible.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University provides students with a socially rich experience immersed in nature. With over 30 student clubs, it supports cultural and professional development. Sports facilities accommodate activities such as mini football, basketball, and table tennis. The campus hosts seminars, exhibitions, and spring festivals. Artvin’s natural attractions, including Lake Çıldır, Karagöl, and the Kafkasör Highland, enrich student life. Prospective students can enjoy a unique experience both on campus and throughout the city.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Due to its proximity to the Caucasus, Artvin Çoruh University attracts international students. Programs such as Russian Language and Caucasian Languages reflect the region’s cultural diversity. Language courses and orientation programs ease the integration process. The Erasmus+ program promotes international mobility. Campus events help students from different countries connect. The welcoming people of Artvin offer a warm environment for international students. Prospective students will find a supportive community here.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Safety</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University provides basic health services on campus. A nurse and a psychologist are available to offer first aid and mental health support. The campus is monitored 24/7 with security personnel and surveillance cameras. Emergency teams are on standby. Hospitals in the city are also close to the campus. Prospective students can study in a safe and healthy environment.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university is located 3 km from the city center and is easily accessible by public transport. Municipal buses and minibuses operate frequently. Kars Airport is 95 km away, and Ardahan Bus Terminal is 90 km from campus. The university also provides shuttle services. Although Artvin’s mountainous roads can be challenging, transportation connections are well-organized. For prospective students, transportation is a planned and manageable aspect of university life.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Artvin Çoruh University offers guidance through its career center, assisting students with internships and job placements. KYK scholarships and loans provide financial support. Accessibility services are available, including a library awarded the “Orange Flag” for supporting students with disabilities. Academic advising helps guide students on their journey. With these services, prospective students are well-prepared for the future.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-12-28T10:39:01Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-04T10:39:27Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'artvin-coruh-university';
