-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ardahan-uni-1.webp","width":"750","height":"500","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ardahan-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ardahan-university/","name":"Ardahan University","datePublished":"2025-12-27T13:31:19+03:00","dateModified":"2025-12-27T13:31:19+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ardahan-uni-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Ardahan University","keywords":"Ardahan University","datePublished":"2025-12-27T13:31:19+03:00","dateModified":"2025-12-27T13:31:19+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Ardahan University is a public institution located in Ardahan, a city in northeastern Turkey that serves as a gateway to the Caucasus. With its academic","name":"Ardahan University","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ardahan-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ardahan-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ardahan-uni-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ardahan-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University is a public institution located in Ardahan, a city in northeastern Turkey that serves as a gateway to the Caucasus. With its academic programs, a campus surrounded by natural beauty, and region-specific opportunities, the university aims to make a difference in education. This guide offers a comprehensive overview, from the university’s background to campus life.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University was established on May 22, 2008, through Law No. 5765, which amended the Law on the Organization of Higher Education Institutions. Its foundation was officially announced in the Official Gazette on May 22, 2008 (Issue No. 26883). As the first higher education institution in the region, it aims to contribute to Ardahan’s academic, social, and cultural development. The current rector is Prof. Dr. Mehmet Biber, who has held the position since January 2017 (as of March 19, 2025—check official sources for updates). The university’s vision is to become a nationally and internationally recognized center of science. Its mission is to lead regional development by producing and sharing knowledge. With the goal of becoming a bridge to the Caucasus, the university brings the region’s potential together with education.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.ardahan.edu.tr/Website/Default.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ardahan University</a> offers a broad academic portfolio. Faculties include Humanities and Literature, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Engineering, Fine Arts, Health Sciences, and Theology. Vocational schools in Çıldır, Göle, and Posof provide associate degree programs. As of 2025, there are over 40 undergraduate and associate degree programs. Around 370 academic staff (including 17 professors, 28 associate professors, and 105 PhD holders) provide both theoretical and practical education. The Central Research Laboratory is well-equipped for scientific studies. According to YÖK Atlas, 5,546 students studied at the university in the 2021–2022 academic year; this number varies each year. Programs like Erasmus+ and Farabi offer both domestic and international opportunities. For more details, consult the university’s official sources.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main campus, Yenisey Campus, is located in Çamlıçatak, 5 km from the city center. Known for its modern architecture, the campus includes general lecture halls, a library, and laboratories. The library, located on the 4th floor, offers extensive resources for students’ academic needs. Smart classrooms and research labs support its technological infrastructure. Eco-friendly initiatives enhance the campus’s sustainability. Despite Ardahan’s harsh climate, heating systems provide a comfortable learning environment. Prospective students can enjoy both a quality education and a peaceful lifestyle surrounded by nature.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Accommodation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University provides students with various accommodation options. Dormitories run by the Credit and Dormitories Institution (KYK), located near the campus, offer affordable and secure living spaces. These dorms feature 24-hour security, dining facilities, and internet access. The university also guides students in adapting to city life. Although private dormitories are limited, rental housing in the city offers alternatives. After receiving their admission, students can apply for KYK dormitories. The campus’s location makes accommodation options easily accessible.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University promotes an active social life for students. With over 20 student clubs, it supports both cultural and professional development. Sports facilities cater to activities like football, basketball, and volleyball. The campus hosts seminars, exhibitions, and festivals. Natural and historical sites such as Lake Çıldır, Ardahan Castle, and Devil’s Castle enrich student life. Prospective students can enjoy a university experience that blends academics with nature, both on and off campus. These opportunities also support personal growth.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can visit the <em>Road to Study</em> platform for more information about university life in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to its proximity to the Caucasus, Ardahan University attracts international students. Departments such as Russian Language, Georgian Language, and Caucasian Languages reflect the region’s cultural diversity. The university facilitates integration through language courses and orientation programs. Erasmus+ supports international mobility. Campus events encourage interaction among students from different nationalities. Ardahan’s hospitable population offers a warm welcome, making it a supportive academic community for international students.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Safety</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university provides basic healthcare services on campus. A health unit is available for first aid and emergencies. Psychological counseling supports students’ mental well-being. The campus is secured with 24-hour surveillance and staff. Emergency teams are ready to respond quickly. Students can pursue their education in a safe and healthy environment. Hospitals in the city are also close to the campus.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University is 5 km from the city center and easily accessible by public transport. Municipal buses and minibuses run frequently. Ardahan Bus Terminal is 7 km away, and Kars Airport is 95 km from campus. The university also provides shuttle services to ease transportation. Well-maintained roads ensure convenient travel. For students, this ease of access is a valuable advantage during their education.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ardahan University offers career guidance through its career center, assisting with internships and job placements. Government scholarships and KYK loans provide financial aid. Accessibility services are available for students with disabilities. Academic advising and mentoring guide students along their journey. With these services, prospective students are well-prepared for their future.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-12-27T10:31:19Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-04T10:34:45Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'ardahan-university';
