ype":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bahcesehir-university.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bahcesehir-university.webp","width":"700","height":"500","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/bahcesehir-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/bahcesehir-university/","name":"Bahçeşehir University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-11-08T17:28:07+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-08T17:28:07+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bahcesehir-university.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Bahçeşehir University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Bahçeşehir University","datePublished":"2025-11-08T17:28:07+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-08T17:28:07+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Bahçeşehir University was established in Istanbul on January 18, 1998, by the Bahçeşehir Uğur Educational Foundation and was officially recognized under Law","name":"Bahçeşehir University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/bahcesehir-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/bahcesehir-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bahcesehir-university.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/bahcesehir-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University was established in Istanbul on January 18, 1998, by the Bahçeşehir Uğur Educational Foundation and was officially recognized under Law No. 3437. As one of Turkey’s leading foundation universities, Bahçeşehir University began offering education in the 1998–1999 academic year, aiming to provide education at international standards. Under the leadership of Rector Prof. Dr. Esra Hatipoğlu (since 2020), the university embraces the vision of being a “world-class university.” Its mission is to educate innovative, research-oriented individuals who contribute to global values. With around 25,000 students (YÖK Atlas, 2022–2023), the university ranked in the 601–800 band in the Times Higher Education 2025 rankings. Bahçeşehir University stands out with its global networks.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University offers education through 9 faculties: Medicine, Dentistry, Engineering and Natural Sciences, Economics, Administrative and Social Sciences, Communication, Law, Educational Sciences, Health Sciences, and Architecture and Design. The university also includes 3 institutes (Science, Social Sciences, Education), 1 conservatory, and 2 vocational schools. There are over 100 undergraduate and graduate programs. Medicine and Engineering are notable for their English-medium instruction. Around 1,000 faculty members provide both theoretical and practical education. More than 50 laboratories and the BAU Medical Park Hospitals support hands-on training. The CO-OP program helps integrate students into the business world. For more information, please visit the official <a href="https://bau.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bahçeşehir University</a> website.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University’s main campus is the South Campus, located by the Bosphorus in Beşiktaş. Additional campuses are in Göztepe, Galata, and the North Campus. The university has over 200,000 m² of indoor space equipped with high-speed internet and smart classrooms. The library offers access to over 150,000 printed materials and more than one million digital publications, with a seating capacity of 1,000. The Faculty of Medicine is integrated with the BAU Medical Park Hospital. The Technology Transfer Office and research labs support innovative projects. The campuses provide robust infrastructure for scientific research and applied learning. Bahçeşehir University stands out with its technological resources.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Dormitories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University offers dormitory facilities near its Beşiktaş and Göztepe campuses. Dormitories have over 1,500 beds in rooms accommodating 1 to 4 students, including beds, wardrobes, desks, bathrooms, and internet access. Facilities include laundry rooms, kitchens, and study areas. Security is ensured by 24/7 camera systems and regular cleaning services. Canteens and cafes meet daily needs. Applications are accepted online, with priority given to scholarship students. In addition, KYK and private dormitory options are available. The dormitories offer convenience due to their proximity to campus.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University offers a vibrant social life. The Beşiktaş Campus provides a peaceful setting with its Bosphorus view, sports fields, and relaxation areas. Sports facilities include courts for basketball, volleyball, and fitness centers, and university teams participate in tournaments. Dining halls serve daily meals, including vegan options. With over 100 student clubs (such as Music, Theater, and Entrepreneurship), the university hosts concerts and the “Spring Fest.” Being located in central Istanbul also allows easy access to cultural events. Welcome events are organized for international students. Bahçeşehir University is known for its strong social opportunities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students seeking more information about university life in Turkey can visit the Road to Study platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University hosts over 5,000 international students from more than 120 countries. Through the BAU Global network, the university maintains connections with campuses in the U.S., Germany, and Canada. The International Office provides visa assistance and orientation programs. Turkish language courses are optional, and 80% of programs are taught in English. The university collaborates with more than 200 institutions through Erasmus+ and bilateral agreements. “International Day” events promote cultural exchange. A mentoring system helps new students adapt to campus life. Istanbul’s cosmopolitan environment offers a unique experience for international students.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Security</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University provides integrated health services through BAU Medical Park Hospitals. On-campus health centers offer check-ups and emergency care, with 24/7 ambulance support. The Psychological Counseling Unit provides individual therapy sessions; appointments can be booked online. Security is ensured 24/7 through surveillance cameras and on-site personnel; entry and exit points are monitored. Fire drills are held regularly, and all buildings are equipped with emergency exits. The university maintains high standards in both health and safety.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University’s Beşiktaş Campus is accessible by ferry, bus (43R, 58N), and shared taxis (dolmuş). Göztepe Campus is near Kadıköy and reachable via metro (M4) and metrobus. Galata Campus is located along the T1 tram line. Campus shuttle services are free. Bicycle paths and parking areas are available. The university is 40 kilometers from Istanbul Airport and offers discounted public transport. Transportation between campuses is convenient.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University provides internship and employment opportunities through its Career Center and organizes “Career Days.” Academic advisors guide students throughout their studies. The Psychological Support Unit offers free therapy. The Disability Support Office ensures accessibility arrangements. The Scholarship Office manages merit- and need-based scholarships and supports students through its mentoring program.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-11-08T14:28:07Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-04T14:30:36Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'bahcesehir-university';
