t","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/avrasya-universitesi-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/avrasya-universitesi-1.webp","width":"1600","height":"900","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/avrasya-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/avrasya-university/","name":"Avrasya University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-11-05T17:08:20+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-05T17:08:20+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/avrasya-universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Avrasya University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Avrasya University","datePublished":"2025-11-05T17:08:20+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-05T17:08:20+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Avrasya University was founded in 2010 in Trabzon as a foundation (vakıf) university. Established by the Trabzon Education, Culture and Health Foundation, it","name":"Avrasya University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/avrasya-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/avrasya-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/avrasya-universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/avrasya-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://avrasya.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Avrasya University</a> was founded in 2010 in Trabzon as a foundation (vakıf) university. Established by the Trabzon Education, Culture and Health Foundation, it became the first foundation university in the Black Sea Region. The university aims to contribute to the region’s and Turkey’s educational landscape by prioritizing quality in education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university’s vision is to train qualified, research-oriented individuals, contribute to regional development, and become a higher education institution recognized internationally. Avrasya University stands out with its modern approach to education and student-centered philosophy.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Located in Trabzon&#8217;s historical and cultural setting, the university offers an environment where students are supported both academically and socially. By blending the dynamic spirit of the Black Sea region with education, it draws attention with its innovative approach and strong academic staff.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University offers a wide range of academic programs at undergraduate, associate, and graduate levels. Its academic structure includes the Faculty of Health Sciences, Faculty of Engineering and Architecture, Faculty of Economics, Administrative and Social Sciences, and the Faculty of Education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main language of instruction is Turkish, with some programs offered in English. International students can join an optional English preparatory program. Especially strong in health sciences and engineering, the university uses practical training models to prepare students for professional life.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Exchange programs such as Erasmus+ and Mevlana provide students with opportunities to study abroad. The academic staff is composed of internationally experienced and specialized faculty. By combining theoretical courses with hands-on practice, Avrasya University provides a rich academic experience.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University operates multiple campuses across Trabzon, including Pelitli, Yalıncak, and Ömer Yıldız campuses. These modern campuses with social spaces offer a comfortable and contemporary learning environment.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Facilities include spacious classrooms, computer labs, workshops, and research centers. Especially in engineering and health sciences, well-equipped labs support practical learning. The library provides access to both print and digital resources to support academic work.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Digital learning platforms allow easy access to online course materials. High-speed internet is available throughout the campuses. Social areas on campus provide students with spaces to relax and engage in extracurricular activities.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Dormitories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University does not have its own dormitories. However, public (KYK) and private dormitories are available near the campuses. KYK dorms offer affordable options with internet, security, meals, and study areas.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Private dormitories provide comfortable living with various pricing options. Most offer internet, security, dining halls, and study rooms. Their proximity to the campus makes transportation easy.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can get information about dormitories and accommodation from the International Relations Office. Trabzon’s student-friendly atmosphere and affordable living costs make accommodation easier. Rental apartments near the campuses are also safe and economical alternatives.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University has a vibrant campus culture that supports student clubs and social events. Clubs organize social responsibility projects, cultural events, and academic seminars to promote student development.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Spring Festivals, concerts, cultural events, and sports tournaments are held annually to make campus life more dynamic. Sports facilities, open-air spaces, and social venues encourage physical activity.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Trabzon’s cultural heritage and natural beauty offer many off-campus social opportunities. Historical sites, parks, and traditional activities help students connect with the city. International students can visit the Road to Study platform for more information about university life in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University offers a welcoming atmosphere for international students, shaped by Trabzon’s cultural diversity and history. The International Relations Office assists newcomers with registration, course selection, visa procedures, and residence permits.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Orientation programs provide information about campus life, transportation, events, and academic procedures to help international students adapt quickly.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student clubs, social projects, cultural events, and technical trips help students from different countries connect. The warm attitude of the local community and Trabzon’s traditions make social integration easier. Tours to historical sites and cultural events allow students to experience Black Sea culture firsthand.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Security</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University prioritizes student health and safety. The on-campus health unit offers basic health services and first aid. For more comprehensive care, the university collaborates with local hospitals.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can benefit from public health services through Turkey’s General Health Insurance (GSS). The International Relations Office provides guidance on the insurance process. Health awareness seminars are held regularly on campus.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Security is maintained 24/7 with security personnel and surveillance systems. Entry points are monitored closely, and safety protocols are strictly applied. The university’s precautions and the overall safety of Trabzon ensure a peaceful learning environment.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University’s campuses are well-connected throughout Trabzon, offering excellent transportation options. Public buses, minibuses, and shared taxis (dolmuş) provide frequent service between campuses and the city center.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students can use the Trabzon Card for discounted fares on public transportation. Bus stops are conveniently located for easy access. The university also provides shuttle services between campuses.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university is approximately 5 km from Trabzon Airport, accessible by public transport or taxi. There are also direct bus routes from the Trabzon Bus Terminal to the campuses. The central location and robust transport system make commuting easy for students.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Avrasya University offers a wide range of services to support academic and personal development. The International Relations Office assists international students with registration, visa applications, health insurance, and residence permits.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Psychological Counseling and Guidance Center provides individual and group support for issues like adaptation, exam stress, and personal growth.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Career Development Center helps students prepare for the workforce with career planning workshops, CV writing sessions, and mock interviews. Through partnerships with local businesses, students can access internship opportunities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic advising offers one-on-one support with course selection, study strategies, and exam preparation. These services aim to enhance academic success and support students in achieving their career goals.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-11-05T14:08:20Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-04T14:12:51Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'avrasya-university';
