 in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankara-sosyal-bilimler-universitesi-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankara-sosyal-bilimler-universitesi-1.webp","width":"853","height":"479","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ankara-social-sciences-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ankara-social-sciences-university/","name":"Ankara Social Sciences University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-11-03T13:30:55+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-03T13:30:56+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankara-sosyal-bilimler-universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Ankara Social Sciences University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Ankara Social Sciences University","datePublished":"2025-11-03T13:30:55+03:00","dateModified":"2025-11-03T13:30:56+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Ankara Social Sciences University (ASBU) is a public university established in Ankara in 2013. As one of Turkey’s first state universities specializing in the","name":"Ankara Social Sciences University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ankara-social-sciences-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ankara-social-sciences-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankara-sosyal-bilimler-universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ankara-social-sciences-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.asbu.edu.tr" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.asbu.edu.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ankara Social Sciences University (ASBU)</a> is a public university established in Ankara in 2013. As one of Turkey’s first state universities specializing in the social sciences, ASBU is recognized for its education and research activities focused on this field.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university’s vision is to generate high-quality knowledge in the social sciences and contribute to social development through scientific research. ASBU aims to provide students with a multidimensional perspective by offering integrated programs across various disciplines of the social sciences. Its academic research is directed towards proposing solutions to social issues, with the goal of becoming an internationally recognized center for social sciences.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Since its establishment, ASBU has rapidly developed, adopting a student-centered educational approach and becoming a key academic hub for those wishing to specialize in the social sciences. Its central location in Ankara allows students to develop both academically and socially.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ankara Social Sciences University offers a wide range of academic programs at undergraduate, graduate, and doctoral levels. Its academic structure includes faculties such as the Faculty of Social and Human Sciences, Faculty of Political Science, Faculty of Foreign Languages, and Faculty of Islamic Studies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The language of instruction is generally Turkish and English, with some programs also offered in Arabic. An English preparatory program is available for international students. ASBU provides multilingual education to help students gain global-level knowledge and skills.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The academic staff consists of experienced faculty members actively involved in national and international projects in the field of social sciences. The education model combines theoretical knowledge with fieldwork and research projects. Students also have opportunities to study and intern abroad through Erasmus+ and Mevlana exchange programs.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU’s campus is located in the Hacı Bayram Veli district, a historic part of Ankara. Its proximity to the city center provides students easy access to social and cultural events. The campus blends modern and historical buildings, offering a rich academic and social environment.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The campus includes modern classrooms, computer labs, research centers, and a comprehensive library. The library offers extensive resources in the field of social sciences and access to digital databases. Students can quickly access up-to-date sources through the online library system.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">High-speed internet is available campus-wide. Computer labs and study areas help students make productive use of their free time. The university’s technological infrastructure is supported by digital learning platforms and online course materials.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Housing</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU does not operate its own dormitories. However, KYK (Credit and Dormitories Institution) dorms and private dormitories are available around the campus. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/private-state-dormitories/">KYK dorms</a> offer essential services such as security, internet, meals, and study areas.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to its central location, students can easily reach various dormitories and student apartments in the city. They can also receive guidance on safe and reliable housing options from the university&#8217;s advisory services.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can consult the ASBU International Relations Office for support in accommodation matters. In addition, rental apartments and student houses around the campus provide affordable and comfortable living options. Ankara’s student-friendly environment and the diversity of accommodation choices make it easier for international students to adapt.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Social Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its focus on social sciences, ASBU encourages student clubs and academic communities. These clubs organize seminars, cultural events, and discussion platforms that support students&#8217; academic development.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Annual student events and cultural festivals bring vibrancy to campus life. Conferences, workshops, and research days in the field of social sciences help students integrate into the academic community.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ankara&#8217;s rich cultural and historical environment offers students a social life filled with museums, art galleries, and historic sites. Social spaces and cafes around the campus allow students to enjoy their free time. International students seeking more information about university education in Turkey can visit the <em>Road to Study</em> platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Adaptation for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU places great importance on the integration process of international students with its multicultural structure and social sciences-oriented academic programs. The International Relations Office guides students through registration, course selection, visa procedures, and residence permits.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university organizes orientation programs to ease students&#8217; adaptation to both the university and the city of Ankara. These programs offer information on Ankara’s cultural and historical background, transportation, and social opportunities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student clubs, social science-themed events, cultural tours, and international celebrations promote interaction among students from different countries. Ankara&#8217;s multicultural atmosphere allows students to integrate easily with the local community. Workshops and talks in the field of social sciences contribute to students’ academic and social development.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Safety</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU prioritizes student health and safety. A health unit on campus offers basic medical services and first aid. For more comprehensive health needs, students are referred to state and private hospitals in Ankara’s central area.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can benefit from Turkey’s public healthcare system at an affordable rate through the General Health Insurance (GSS). The International Relations Office supports students in applying for health insurance. Health information sessions organized by the health unit help raise awareness about healthcare services.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Campus safety is ensured with 24/7 security personnel and surveillance cameras. Entry and exit points are regularly monitored, and strict security measures are in place. The campus’s central location and security infrastructure provide a peaceful learning environment.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU’s city-center campus offers easy access to public transportation, including metro, buses, and minibuses. Ulus Metro Station is within walking distance, making transportation within the city highly convenient.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students can use the <em>AnkaraKart</em> to benefit from discounted public transport fares. Nearby bus stops on major city routes allow for easy travel to other districts. The university provides transport guidance to help new students navigate the city comfortably.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The campus is about 30 kilometers from Ankara Esenboğa Airport and can be reached via airport shuttles or taxis. Direct bus and metro connections are also available from Ankara’s main bus terminal (AŞTİ). The central campus location makes it easy to get around the city.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ASBU provides comprehensive services to support students’ academic, social, and personal development. The International Relations Office offers guidance to international students in registration, visa applications, health insurance, and residence permits.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Psychological Counseling and Guidance Center provides individual support for issues like adjustment, exam anxiety, stress management, and personal development. One-on-one sessions and group activities organized by professional counselors help promote student well-being.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Career Development Center supports students with career planning, job search strategies, and internship opportunities. Workshops on resume writing, interview techniques, and career planning help students transition into professional life. Social sciences-themed seminars and career days also help students build industry connections.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic advising services offer personalized guidance in course selection and academic progress. These services help students succeed in their academic journey. ASBU, with its focus on social sciences, ensures that students develop into well-equipped individuals through strong academic support services.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-11-03T10:30:55Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-11-03T10:30:56Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'ankara-social-sciences-university';
