tudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amasya-university.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amasya-university.webp","width":"834","height":"556","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/amasya-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/amasya-university/","name":"Amasya University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-10-30T14:58:46+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-30T14:58:47+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amasya-university.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Amasya University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Amasya University","datePublished":"2025-10-30T14:58:46+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-30T14:58:47+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Amasya University is a public university established on March 17, 2006, in Amasya, Turkey, by Law No. 5467. The university aims to contribute to research,","name":"Amasya University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/amasya-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/amasya-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amasya-university.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/amasya-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University is a public university established on March 17, 2006, in Amasya, Turkey, by Law No. 5467. The university aims to contribute to research, education, healthcare, and learning in line with universal, scientific, and ethical values to help position Turkey as a leading force in the modern world.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University offers a wide range of academic programs through its various faculties and schools. These include the Faculties of Education, Arts and Sciences, Engineering, Theology, Architecture, Health Sciences, and Merzifon Faculty of Economics and Administrative Sciences. Additionally, the university has several vocational schools and graduate institutes providing undergraduate and postgraduate programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Its academic staff consists of experienced and qualified faculty members. The university combines theoretical knowledge with practical applications to support students’ professional and personal development.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more detailed information, please visit the official website of <a href="https://www.amasya.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Amasya University.</a></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University operates across several campuses equipped with modern and technological facilities. These campuses include libraries, laboratories, workshops, and research centers. The university places strong emphasis on sustainability and eco-friendly practices, carrying out projects focused on energy efficiency and waste management.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Housing</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A variety of accommodation options are available for Amasya University students. KYK (Credit and Dormitories Institution) dormitories provide safe and affordable housing, including facilities such as breakfast and dinner services, common areas, sports halls, swimming pools, cafeterias, study and relaxation rooms, and social spaces.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Private dormitories and student apartments also offer alternative housing options. For instance, Amasya Academic Apart provides secure accommodation with 24/7 camera surveillance and is located close to the university.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University offers a rich social and cultural environment for students. Student clubs and societies organize events, seminars, and workshops throughout the year, helping students explore their interests and develop their skills.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On-campus concerts, theater performances, and exhibitions encourage artistic and cultural participation, while sports facilities and tournaments promote physical activity.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The city of Amasya offers students a peaceful setting with its historical and natural beauty, cultural events, and relaxed lifestyle. Students also have the opportunity to explore local culture and expand their social networks through various city events.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more about university life in Turkey, international students can visit the Road to Study platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Adaptation for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University welcomes students from various countries. The International Student Office organizes orientation programs, language courses, and cultural activities to help international students adapt to university life.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Language courses are offered by TÖMER (Turkish and Foreign Languages Research and Application Center) for those who wish to learn Turkish. Additionally, seminars and cultural tours are organized to introduce students to Turkish culture and traditions.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Through Erasmus+ and other international exchange programs, students have the opportunity to study and intern abroad. These experiences enhance global awareness and encourage intercultural interaction.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Security</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University prioritizes student health and safety. On-campus health units provide basic medical services and refer students to hospitals when necessary. Psychological counseling services are also available to support students’ mental well-being.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Campus security is maintained through 24/7 surveillance and trained security personnel. Crisis management plans are in place to ensure a safe learning environment for all students.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University has campuses in various districts, including the Central Campus, Sabuncuoğlu Şerefeddin, Technical Campus, Taşova, Merzifon, Gümüşhacıköy, and Suluova. These campuses are easily accessible via local minibuses and buses. The city&#8217;s public transportation network allows students to travel conveniently between campuses and the city center.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For students arriving from outside the city, Amasya Merzifon Airport—located about 45 minutes from the city center—offers a significant transportation advantage. The university is also easily accessible by road from nearby provinces such as Samsun and Tokat.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bus and minibus stops near campuses provide quick and safe access, and university-operated shuttle services support transportation during peak hours.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Amasya University offers a wide range of student-centered support services. The Career Development Application and Research Center (KAGEM) helps students plan their careers before and after graduation through job/internship postings, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-cv-hazirlama-ipuclari/" data-type="post" data-id="8797">CV preparation workshops</a>, career seminars, and employer meetups.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Various scholarships are available for students in need of financial assistance, including merit-based, need-based, and KYK scholarships, as well as social support grants. The university also provides meal scholarships and stationery aid.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In line with its &#8220;Accessible University&#8221; principle, Amasya University supports students with disabilities through improved physical access, academic material support, and personalized counseling. All university units are structured to accommodate students with special needs, and efforts are ongoing to make campuses fully accessible.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Psychological Counseling and Guidance Unit provides students with professional support in areas such as exam anxiety and stress management, contributing to their personal development.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-10-30T11:58:46Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-10-30T11:58:47Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'amasya-university';
