roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/altinbas_universitesi-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/altinbas_universitesi-1.webp","width":"1280","height":"720","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/altinbas-university/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/altinbas-university/","name":"Altınbaş University - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-10-30T14:48:25+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-30T14:48:31+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/altinbas_universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a3c0f700b03ed22f8ab3a40880c2b539035a9a6e21bb16550f65e22a0ff39809?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"busra","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"Article","headline":"Altınbaş University - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Altınbaş University","datePublished":"2025-10-30T14:48:25+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-30T14:48:31+03:00","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/busra/","name":"busra"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Altınbaş University was established in Istanbul in 2008 by the Mehmet Altınbaş Education and Culture Foundation, originally under the name “Istanbul","name":"Altınbaş University - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/altinbas-university/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/altinbas-university/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/altinbas_universitesi-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/altinbas-university/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading">History and Vision of the University</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University was established in Istanbul in 2008 by the Mehmet Altınbaş Education and Culture Foundation, originally under the name “Istanbul Kemerburgaz University.” The institution was renamed Altınbaş University through a decree published in the Official Gazette on July 1, 2017, in line with the late businessman Mehmet Altınbaş’s wish to invest in education. With its founding rector Prof. Dr. İsmail Özaslan, the university welcomed its first students in the 2011–2012 academic year.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Currently led by Rector Prof. Dr. Ali Argun Karacabey (since 2024), the university operates with the vision of “Science, Unity, Success,” aiming to provide education at international standards and to cultivate entrepreneurial and innovative individuals. It focuses especially on becoming a leader in the fields of technology and healthcare. With approximately 10,000 students (2022–2023 YÖK Atlas), Altınbaş University ranked in the 601–800 band in the Times Higher Education 2025 rankings and stands out among Turkey’s foundation universities. With strong academic backgrounds in engineering, medicine, and business, the university distinguishes itself through global partnerships.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University offers a broad academic portfolio through its 10 faculties: Medicine, Dentistry, Pharmacy, Engineering and Natural Sciences, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Law, Fine Arts and Design, Communication, Business, and Applied Sciences. There is also one graduate school (Institute of Graduate Studies) and two vocational schools (Health Services and Justice). The university offers over 30 undergraduate programs, 34 associate degree programs, 28 master&#8217;s programs, and 6 doctoral programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">English is the primary language of instruction, especially in prominent programs such as Medicine, Software Engineering, and Business. Around 500 faculty members combine theoretical knowledge with hands-on learning. With more than 50 laboratories and 15 research centers (e.g., AU INOVA), the university conducts advanced scientific research. Students are prepared for the professional world through internships and project-based learning. Altınbaş University holds international accreditations (e.g., MÜDEK), certifying the quality of its education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, please refer to the official resources of <a href="https://www.altinbas.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Altınbaş University</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Campus and Technological Infrastructure</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university’s main campus is the Mahmutbey Technology Campus, located in Bağcılar, a district considered one of Istanbul’s technology hubs. Other campuses include the Gayrettepe Campus (for Social Sciences) and the Bakırköy Campus (Health Sciences). With a total of 150,000 m² of indoor space, the campuses are equipped with high-speed internet, smart classrooms, and state-of-the-art laboratories. The library provides access to over 50,000 e-books, 19,000 e-journals, and 25 databases. The media center supports HD broadcasting. The sports center includes a gym, tennis courts, and fitness areas, supporting students’ physical well-being.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Technology Transfer Office strengthens cooperation with the industry, while the centrally located campuses provide a modern learning environment. The Mahmutbey Campus stands out with its sustainability-focused design and energy efficiency.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Housing</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University offers on-campus housing at the Mahmutbey Campus. The dormitory accommodates 500 students, with 1–4 person rooms equipped with beds, wardrobes, desks, and high-speed internet. Shared facilities include laundry rooms, kitchens, and study areas. Security is ensured with 24/7 surveillance and personnel; cleaning services are provided regularly. Public (KYK) and private dormitories are also available, with priority given to fully funded scholarship students. Dormitory fees vary by room type, and financial aid packages may be available.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Life</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University offers a dynamic and vibrant student life. The green spaces, sports fields, and modern environment create a peaceful atmosphere on campus. The sports center, basketball courts, fitness areas, and dance studios encourage physical activity. Dining halls provide healthy and varied meals, while on-campus cafés serve as social hubs. With over 60 student clubs (e.g., Entrepreneurship, Arts, Technology), the university hosts festivals, concerts, and seminars.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Istanbul’s rich cultural scene, including museums and events, further enhances student life. For international students, orientation days and cultural trips are organized to encourage integration and intercultural exchange.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To learn more about university life in Turkey, international students can visit the Road to Study platform.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Cultural Integration for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University hosts nearly 5,000 international students from 89 countries, making up around 40% of the student population a high ratio among Turkey’s foundation universities. The International Office offers comprehensive support with visa applications, residence permits, and orientation programs. Turkish language courses are provided by TOMER, while most academic programs are conducted in English.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Through Erasmus+ and other exchange programs, the university collaborates with over 150 institutions worldwide, giving students global exposure. “International Day” events promote cultural interaction and a multicultural atmosphere on campus. Istanbul’s cosmopolitan nature facilitates the integration of international students and supports their social inclusion.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Health Services and Security</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University provides basic healthcare services on campus through its Health Center, along with 24/7 ambulance services. The School of Medicine is affiliated with a Teaching and Research Hospital in Bakırköy, delivering advanced medical services. The Psychological Counseling Unit offers free individual therapy sessions, with appointments available online.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Campus security is maintained with 24-hour surveillance systems and professional security personnel, with controlled entry and exit points. Emergency preparedness measures are in place, and students are encouraged to have health insurance coverage.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Transportation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Mahmutbey Technology Campus is a 5-minute walk from Mahmutbey Metro Station and is also accessible via bus and minibus routes. The Gayrettepe Campus is near <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-transportation-discounts-in-turkey/">metro and metrobus lines</a>, while the Bakırköy Campus is close to sea buses and IDO piers. The campus is 40 kilometers from Istanbul Airport and 15 kilometers from Esenler Bus Terminal. Students benefit from discounted public transportation cards. Free shuttle services between campuses also facilitate transportation.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Student Support Services</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Altınbaş University offers internship and job opportunities through its Career Center, organizing Career Days and employer meetings. Academic advisors support students in their academic journey and course selections. The Psychological Support Unit provides therapy for stress management and personal development. The Accessible Altınbaş Unit ensures campus accessibility for students with special needs. The Scholarship Office coordinates merit-based and need-based scholarships, with fully funded students benefiting from both tuition and dormitory services.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-10-30T11:48:25Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2025-10-30T11:48:31Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'altinbas-university';
